ds designed and automatically adapts desktop sites and web apps to touch in order to deliver a rich browsing experience. Learn how your site or embedded WebView can take advantage of powerful new features and coding best practices to deliver a best-in class user experience for iPad."}],"kind":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-203-Introducing-Desktopclass-Browsing-on-iPad","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-203-introducing-desktopclass-browsing-on-ipad","title":"Introducing Desktop-class Browsing on iPad","role":"sampleCode"},"Blackjacx":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/Blackjacx.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":"Profile image of Stefan Herold","type":"image","identifier":"Blackjacx"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19-513-Understanding-CPU-Usage-with-Web-Inspector":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"As a developer of web content, you play an important role in fulfilling customer expectations for a high performance web experience while minimizing power use across all their devices. Discover new insights on how you can improve the power efficiency of your webpages in Safari, or embedded web content in your apps, by using this powerful new tool in Web Inspector. Learn new strategies to help you deliver dynamic experiences that use less CPU and save battery life."}],"kind":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-513-Understanding-CPU-Usage-with-Web-Inspector","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-513-understanding-cpu-usage-with-web-inspector","title":"Understanding CPU Usage with Web Inspector","role":"sampleCode"},"WWDC19-Icon.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDC19-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null,"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC19-Icon.png"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null,"type":"image","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"},"https://developer.apple.com/wwd